6
00:01:47,281 --> 00:01:49,693
It's not the money, go ahead if you want,

7
00:01:49,795 --> 00:01:53,686
but don't expect me to be part of it.

8
00:01:54,311 --> 00:01:56,575
What are you saying?

9
00:01:56,601 --> 00:01:59,457
To put it bluntly,

10
00:01:59,515 --> 00:02:02,325
I'd rather be with them than you.

11
00:02:02,438 --> 00:02:05,294
You both look about the same in size,

12
00:02:05,359 --> 00:02:06,963
but at least there's some novelty in them.

13
00:02:07,280 --> 00:02:11,296
When I met you, you said you'd bring me
fortune and children.

14
00:02:11,320 --> 00:02:13,459
Am I rich? In my dreams!

15
00:02:13,477 --> 00:02:15,377
You can't even lay an egg.

16
00:02:15,399 --> 00:02:16,298
Stop lying to me.

17
00:02:16,358 --> 00:02:17,371
You said I shouldn't con people,

18
00:02:17,398 --> 00:02:18,445
or my children will get retribution.

19
00:02:18,522 --> 00:02:20,445
But you're the biggest con artist,

20
00:02:20,522 --> 00:02:21,535
liar of the century!

21
00:02:21,610 --> 00:02:25,888
Con artist, liar...

22
00:02:28,874 --> 00:02:30,763
Don't have a fit over this!

23
00:02:31,921 --> 00:02:35,971
We're out of soya sauce. I'll go get it.

24
00:02:39,155 --> 00:02:41,021
This is good, Sis.

25
00:02:44,560 --> 00:02:52,684
What are you eating? Alright...

26
00:03:03,029 --> 00:03:05,248
Excuse me, auntie.

27
00:03:09,795 --> 00:03:15,325
Auntie? Do I look that old?

28
00:03:20,200 --> 00:03:22,760
Fatty! What a coincidence!

29
00:03:24,671 --> 00:03:26,662
What's wrong? You're all teary-eyed!

30
00:03:28,201 --> 00:03:30,932
My husband doesn't want me!

31
00:03:39,232 --> 00:03:40,768
It's OK! Thanks!

32
00:03:42,231 --> 00:03:43,221
She removed her husband's name.

33
00:03:43,279 --> 00:03:45,964
Is she divorced or is he dead?

34
00:03:46,030 --> 00:03:49,216
Have you ever seen her husband? I haven't.

35
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:52,250
I know she has 2 sons who are
quite good looking.

36
00:03:52,514 --> 00:03:55,324
The picture on her desk? I know that.

37
00:03:55,387 --> 00:03:57,856
She's always so secretive, what a weirdo!

38
00:03:57,996 --> 00:03:59,612
That's enough!

39
00:04:07,028 --> 00:04:11,124
Mrs Lam...Sorry, Miss Luk.

40
00:04:11,199 --> 00:04:12,940
You have 10 minutes before the
press conference.

41
00:04:12,997 --> 00:04:14,453
LY wants to know if you're ready.

42
00:04:14,483 --> 00:04:16,303
Tell him I'm ready.

43
00:04:16,999 --> 00:04:21,129
I must admit, today's media
have more sources,

44
00:04:21,154 --> 00:04:23,577
and more channels of distribution.

45
00:04:23,637 --> 00:04:25,685
That's why their reaction to each story

46
00:04:25,746 --> 00:04:27,612
is much quicker than the Government.

47
00:04:27,669 --> 00:04:29,125
Our colleagues of the Resource Centre

48
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:31,009
only wish to verify it.

49
00:04:31,107 --> 00:04:34,452
I emphasise we have no intention
to interfere with the freedom of the press.

50
00:04:34,512 --> 00:04:37,095
You think this is strictly a human error?

51
00:04:37,278 --> 00:04:38,689
Because Mrs Lam was at karaoke.

52
00:04:38,716 --> 00:04:40,525
That's why the press release was late?

53
00:04:40,591 --> 00:04:43,128
Incorrect account of an incident
may constitute libel.

54
00:04:43,155 --> 00:04:44,737
We have pictures to prove it.

55
00:04:44,757 --> 00:04:46,657
Unless Mrs Lam doesn't recognise herself.

56
00:04:49,995 --> 00:04:51,167
Care to comment, Mrs Lam?

57
00:04:51,231 --> 00:04:53,245
I heard you became single again recently.

58
00:04:53,309 --> 00:04:54,970
Is that why you went drinking?

59
00:04:55,029 --> 00:04:56,372
LY is your boss.

60
00:04:56,397 --> 00:04:58,047
Did he spend time to console you?

61
00:04:58,107 --> 00:05:01,088
Mrs Lam and I will not answer
any personal questions.

62
00:05:01,114 --> 00:05:02,684
Rumour has it you'll quit your job
to run for councillor.

63
00:05:02,714 --> 00:05:04,648
Will you two work hand in hand?

64
00:05:04,715 --> 00:05:05,932
That's a personal question.

65
00:05:05,958 --> 00:05:07,323
Rumour has it after you leave
the Government,

66
00:05:07,388 --> 00:05:08,890
you will go into politics.

67
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:12,652
As your star assistant, will Mrs Lam
follow you?

68
00:05:12,717 --> 00:05:15,687
That's all for today. Thank you.

69
00:05:16,153 --> 00:05:17,211
<i>Wait...</i>

70
00:05:17,240 --> 00:05:19,220
Mrs Lam, care to comment?

71
00:05:19,279 --> 00:05:22,579
Mrs Lam, say a few words...

72
00:05:24,794 --> 00:05:27,729
Come into my office. I want a word with you.

73
00:05:30,230 --> 00:05:31,971
Are you really that stupid?

74
00:05:32,028 --> 00:05:35,248
You knew karaokes are flooded
with reporters.

75
00:05:35,310 --> 00:05:37,404
You let them take pictures of you
when you were blasted,

76
00:05:37,514 --> 00:05:40,370
at a time when you had
just announced your divorce.

77
00:05:40,397 --> 00:05:42,729
You know I hardly go to those places.

78
00:05:42,755 --> 00:05:45,247
It just so happened I went with
my old classmates.

79
00:05:45,308 --> 00:05:46,400
No excuse!

80
00:05:46,434 --> 00:05:47,572
OK...

81
00:05:48,356 --> 00:05:49,653
You should know very well,

82
00:05:49,716 --> 00:05:52,048
what you do affect not only you

83
00:05:52,074 --> 00:05:54,293
but also affect me.

84
00:05:54,558 --> 00:05:57,243
People in politics must
sacrifice their personal lives.

85
00:05:57,277 --> 00:05:59,450
If you want to be the woman
behind me,

86
00:05:59,513 --> 00:06:02,301
you must behave yourself in public.

87
00:06:03,716 --> 00:06:06,504
Don't worry, it won't happen again.

88
00:06:06,559 --> 00:06:07,651
I haven't had a chance to ask you,

89
00:06:07,714 --> 00:06:09,296
you've been divorced for some time.

90
00:06:09,355 --> 00:06:13,041
Why did you choose to announce it now?

91
00:06:13,074 --> 00:06:14,326
Precisely because it has been so long,

92
00:06:14,357 --> 00:06:15,893
I don't want to hide anything anymore.

93
00:06:15,919 --> 00:06:19,526
Don't tell me you were doing it for me.

94
00:06:22,355 --> 00:06:27,759
No, I want no more constraints,
no more secrets.

95
00:06:27,793 --> 00:06:30,376
It has nothing to do with you.

96
00:06:32,950 --> 00:06:35,885
The media will be in hot pursuit.

97
00:06:37,918 --> 00:06:40,046
Except for official business,

98
00:06:40,074 --> 00:06:42,247
it's best we don't see each other.

99
00:06:42,279 --> 00:06:45,249
I won't drop by at night anymore.

100
00:06:48,511 --> 00:06:52,778
You look so cool with that poker face,

101
00:06:53,590 --> 00:06:56,173
I want to eat you alive!

102
00:07:09,154 --> 00:07:12,966
When will you hand in your resignation?

103
00:07:13,278 --> 00:07:15,326
I want to think it over.

104
00:07:15,354 --> 00:07:16,685
I need to make some plans.

105
00:07:17,151 --> 00:07:18,778
I thought we agreed.

106
00:07:18,801 --> 00:07:20,610
What's there to plan?

107
00:07:20,949 --> 00:07:25,170
You know if I quit now, I'll lose everything

108
00:07:25,199 --> 00:07:28,248
housing, medical insurance, pension...

109
00:07:28,356 --> 00:07:30,734
My sons are still in school in the UK.

110
00:07:30,792 --> 00:07:32,658
I don't want them affected.

111
00:07:32,714 --> 00:07:36,969
I need you to help me set up the office.

112
00:07:37,154 --> 00:07:40,010
You know how long I have been
planning for this.

113
00:07:40,074 --> 00:07:44,932
I can only make this happen with your help.

114
00:07:44,956 --> 00:07:46,219
You can't be so selfish

115
00:07:46,276 --> 00:07:48,210
and only think of yourself.

116
00:07:48,278 --> 00:07:49,962
You have to think of me.

117
00:07:57,667 --> 00:08:01,251
Fine! I get it...

118
00:08:01,308 --> 00:08:04,494
I didn't realise our mutual
trust is so fragile.

119
00:08:04,762 --> 00:08:06,298
Let's pretend nothing happened

120
00:08:06,356 --> 00:08:08,450
and I haven't said anything, OK?

121
00:08:12,356 --> 00:08:14,017
What does that mean?

122
00:08:14,035 --> 00:08:15,503
I said I needed to think about it.

123
00:08:15,520 --> 00:08:16,726
I didn't say I wouldn't help you.

124
00:08:16,792 --> 00:08:19,250
I have work to do. We'll talk later.

125
00:08:19,310 --> 00:08:20,971
You should get back to work too.

126
00:08:21,840 --> 00:08:25,572
OK? OK!

127
00:08:54,666 --> 00:08:55,656
Hey, gorgeous!

128
00:08:59,198 --> 00:09:01,064
Does he have to run off like that?

129
00:09:01,119 --> 00:09:03,497
Can't even stay for a chat?

130
00:09:14,558 --> 00:09:15,889
All by yourself?

131
00:09:21,151 --> 00:09:23,779
It's hot!

132
00:09:38,512 --> 00:09:39,968
Do you mind?

133
00:10:34,948 --> 00:10:37,007
Let's find something to do.

134
00:10:58,636 --> 00:11:05,087
(Chun-lei calling...)

135
00:11:10,791 --> 00:11:12,805
When will you grow up?

136
00:11:12,869 --> 00:11:15,782
Even a kid knows drugs can
ruin your life.

137
00:11:15,837 --> 00:11:19,057
Why don't you kick the habit?

138
00:11:20,790 --> 00:11:23,339
You sound more like my Mom than my Mom.

139
00:11:23,362 --> 00:11:26,650
Mom my foot! How can you laugh?

140
00:11:27,277 --> 00:11:29,291
Are you scared?

141
00:11:29,684 --> 00:11:30,810
Not as much as you should be.

142
00:11:30,870 --> 00:11:32,929
The marijuana fell out of your pocket.

143
00:11:32,956 --> 00:11:35,857
The cops already said they wouldn't
press charges against me.

144
00:11:36,634 --> 00:11:39,376
But after this incident,

145
00:11:39,401 --> 00:11:43,884
I must carry my ID card even when
I take out the garbage.

146
00:11:45,399 --> 00:11:48,334
I'm so glad to see you.

147
00:11:48,361 --> 00:11:50,602
The paperwork is done. Let's go.

148
00:11:52,432 --> 00:11:54,776
Bye, gorgeous! Let's do it again.

149
00:12:11,201 --> 00:12:15,172
Thanks! You were the first name
that came to my head.

150
00:12:15,201 --> 00:12:16,885
After all you're a government official.

151
00:12:22,357 --> 00:12:26,214
Have you eaten? Happy hour on me?

152
00:12:26,795 --> 00:12:30,572
Why were you arrested?

153
00:12:31,356 --> 00:12:34,656
Pure bad luck! I went out to buy a beer.

154
00:12:34,676 --> 00:12:36,166
The cops asked for my ID

155
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:37,884
and brought me back to the police station.

156
00:12:37,997 --> 00:12:39,886
Don't lie to me.

157
00:12:39,919 --> 00:12:43,605
I really forgot my ID.

158
00:12:43,636 --> 00:12:46,173
You forgot to bring it to check into
a love motel.

159
00:12:46,232 --> 00:12:48,894
Who was that guy? He's a delivery boy!

160
00:12:48,918 --> 00:12:51,762
A delivery boy in possession of marijuana.

161
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:54,400
I can't believe you could be so indiscreet
at your age.

162
00:12:54,435 --> 00:12:56,972
Jenny, what happened to you?

163
00:12:57,590 --> 00:13:00,446
I told you it's bad luck.

164
00:13:00,558 --> 00:13:02,219
I haven't done this in 10 years.

165
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:04,732
I got arrested the minute
I wanted to get laid.

166
00:13:05,076 --> 00:13:06,328
Chatty, believe me...

167
00:13:06,357 --> 00:13:08,371
Sorry, don't call me Chatty on the street.

168
00:13:08,397 --> 00:13:12,686
OK, Mrs Lam. I don't usually do this.

169
00:13:12,746 --> 00:13:15,659
I've been really dry lately,

170
00:13:15,676 --> 00:13:17,804
so I let myself do something so stupid.

171
00:13:17,950 --> 00:13:20,533
You were quite the free spirit
even back then.

172
00:13:20,560 --> 00:13:22,813
You always knew how to had fun.

173
00:13:22,919 --> 00:13:25,502
I can't believe you'd come to this
at your age.

174
00:13:29,636 --> 00:13:31,047
Forget it.

175
00:13:31,512 --> 00:13:35,528
It's late. Go home, take a shower
and go to bed.

176
00:13:36,354 --> 00:13:40,143
Next time, don't call me.

177
00:13:40,276 --> 00:13:42,142
I don't want reporters on my tail.

178
00:13:44,840 --> 00:13:46,934
I'll pay you back later...

179
00:13:53,028 --> 00:13:54,371
Anyway, thank you,

180
00:14:05,666 --> 00:14:08,408
Please leave a message, we'll reply ASAP.

181
00:14:08,589 --> 00:14:12,685
Honey, it's Mom!

182
00:14:13,154 --> 00:14:15,942
Is it cold in the UK?

183
00:14:16,232 --> 00:14:20,214
Big Bro, remind your kid brother
to stay warm.

184
00:14:20,239 --> 00:14:24,142
He has a sensitive windpipe.
It'll mean trouble if he catches a cold.

185
00:14:24,667 --> 00:14:27,807
Call me when you guys get this message.

186
00:14:28,075 --> 00:14:33,093
I really miss you two. Love you.

187
00:14:52,871 --> 00:14:55,294
(Chu-lei calling...)

188
00:14:55,356 --> 00:14:57,575
Hello? Surprised? Mrs Lam

189
00:14:57,635 --> 00:15:02,289
Yuen-chau! Hello? Are you OK, Chatty?

190
00:15:02,355 --> 00:15:05,165
Say something! Hello? What is it?

191
00:15:19,153 --> 00:15:22,168
It's late. What on earth do you want?

192
00:15:22,200 --> 00:15:23,611
Precisely because it's late, I want to
make sure you're OK.

193
00:15:23,667 --> 00:15:25,852
I heard something break. Are you OK?

194
00:15:25,915 --> 00:15:27,326
I'm fine!

195
00:15:30,199 --> 00:15:33,737
You have a nice ﬂat.

196
00:15:33,793 --> 00:15:36,455
Must be nice to be a civil servant.

197
00:15:37,872 --> 00:15:39,783
Why did you get so drunk?

198
00:15:40,277 --> 00:15:43,008
I'm OK!

199
00:15:43,995 --> 00:15:45,326
Drink some water.

200
00:15:48,277 --> 00:15:50,291
Here...

201
00:15:52,511 --> 00:15:57,779
I know him. He's your boss LY.

202
00:15:59,277 --> 00:16:00,859
Your boys are so big!

203
00:16:01,230 --> 00:16:04,609
Just the boys? No pictures of your husband?

204
00:16:05,589 --> 00:16:08,058
I won't answer personal questions.

205
00:16:08,760 --> 00:16:13,163
I'm not Mrs Lam anymore.

206
00:16:13,230 --> 00:16:16,450
No more Lam Luk Yuen-chau.

207
00:16:16,916 --> 00:16:22,423
My name is Luk Yuen-chau. That's me.

208
00:16:25,073 --> 00:16:27,656
No wonder you're drunk!

209
00:16:31,122 --> 00:16:36,174
Your phone is ringing! You have a message.

210
00:16:43,230 --> 00:16:45,210
(LY: I miss the way you moan in bed.)

211
00:16:58,307 --> 00:16:59,172
Chun-lei!

212
00:17:00,431 --> 00:17:02,240
Slow down. There's no hurry.

213
00:17:02,275 --> 00:17:03,731
I can't carry you if you pass out.

214
00:17:03,791 --> 00:17:07,295
Don't tell them about my husband.

215
00:17:07,557 --> 00:17:10,731
Come on, he said you're worse than a hippo.

216
00:17:10,760 --> 00:17:13,889
A creep like that belongs to the landfill.

217
00:17:13,947 --> 00:17:16,928
Don't worry. The girls are on your side.

218
00:17:16,956 --> 00:17:19,687
I know they are.

219
00:17:19,761 --> 00:17:21,138
According to the Book of Reincarnation,

220
00:17:21,161 --> 00:17:23,528
I'm here to pay a debt in this life.

221
00:17:23,559 --> 00:17:25,778
Nothing I can do can change that.

222
00:17:25,801 --> 00:17:28,372
